Q: Update the ubuntu container, install apache and php, then push updated on to docker hub.

The purpose of updating the Ubuntu container, installing Apache and PHP, and pushing it to Docker Hub is to
create a ready-to-use web server environment that is secure, portable, shareable, and deployable on any system.

COmmands:
          STEP 1: Firstly pull the disired image from dockerhub
                    Docker pull ubuntu
          STEP 2: to run the image 
                    Docker run -it --name myubuntu ubuntu
          STEP 3: to update the container
                    #apt update
                    #apt upgrade -y
          STEP 4: to install the apache and php
                    # apt install apache2 -y
                    # apt install php -y
          STEP 5: check wather apache and php is inastall
                    # apache2 -v
                    # php -v
                    # exit
          STEP 6: now tag the image
                    docker tag ubuntu mohtbhau777/update_ubuntu_container:v2
          STEP 7: check the tag 
                    docker images
          STEP 8: push the image to dockerhub
                    docker push mohtbhau777/update_ubuntu_container:v2
